.TH "irq_domain_add_legacy" 9 "irq_domain_add_legacy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
irq_domain_add_legacy \- Allocate and register a legacy revmap irq_domain.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct irq_domain *" irq_domain_add_legacy
.BI "(struct device_node *of_node "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "unsigned int first_irq "  ","
.BI "irq_hw_number_t first_hwirq "  ","
.BI "const struct irq_domain_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "void *host_data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "of_node" 12
pointer to interrupt controller's device tree node.
.IP "size" 12
total number of irqs in legacy mapping
.IP "first_irq" 12
first number of irq block assigned to the domain
.IP "first_hwirq" 12
first hwirq number to use for the translation. Should normally
be '0', but a positive integer can be used if the effective
hwirqs numbering does not begin at zero.
.IP "ops" 12
map/unmap domain callbacks
.IP "host_data" 12
Controller private data pointer
.SH "NOTE"
the \fBmap\fP callback will be called before this function returns
for all legacy interrupts except 0 (which is always the invalid irq for
a legacy controller).
